Load Images¶

In [3]:
# Load Images

sample_data_images = []
for i in notebook.tqdm(range(sample_data_labels.shape[0])):
    path = 'Dataset/Images/'+sample_data_labels['image_name'][i]
    img = image.load_img(path,target_size=(150,150,3))
    img = image.img_to_array(img)
    img = img/255
    sample_data_images.append(img)

Get Dummies¶










In [5]:



     


# Get Dummies

sample_data_images = np.array(sample_data_images)
X = sample_data_images
y = pd.DataFrame()

y['humour'] = sample_data_labels['humour']
y['sarcasm'] = sample_data_labels['sarcasm']
y['offensive'] = sample_data_labels['offensive']
y['motivational'] = sample_data_labels['motivational']

y['humour'].replace({"hilarious":1 , "very_funny": 1, "funny": 1, "not_funny":0}, inplace= True)
y['sarcasm'].replace({"general":0 , "twisted_meaning": 1, "very_twisted": 1, "not_sarcastic":0}, inplace= True)
y['offensive'].replace({"very_offensive":1 , "slight": 0, "hateful_offensive": 1, "not_offensive":0}, inplace= True)
y['motivational'].replace({ "motivational": 1, "not_motivational":0}, inplace= True)
Y = y



     















Build Model¶










In [6]:



     


# Build Model

model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(16,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu',input_shape=X[0].shape))
model.add(BatchNormalization())
model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(32,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu'))
model.add(BatchNormalization())
model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))
model.add(Dropout(0.3))

model.add(Conv2D(64,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='relu'))
model.add(BatchNormalization())
model.add(MaxPool2D(2,2))
model.add(Dropout(0.4))

model.add(Flatten())

model.add(Dense(Y.shape[1],activation='sigmoid'))

Get Predictions¶










In [11]:



     


# Get Predictions

application_window = tk.Tk()
my_filetypes = [('all files', '.*'), ('text files', '.txt')]
user_file = filedialog.askopenfilename(parent=application_window,
                                    initialdir=os.getcwd(),
                                    title="Please select an Image to Detect Humor:",
                                    filetypes=my_filetypes)
application_window.destroy()
user_img = image.load_img(user_file,target_size=(150,150,3))
img = image.img_to_array(user_img)
img = img/255
plt.imshow(user_img)
pred_lab=model.predict(np.array([img]))

prediction = ' | '
if(pred_lab[0][0] > 0.5):
    prediction = prediction + "Funny | "
if(pred_lab[0][1] > 0.5):
    prediction = prediction + "Sarcastic | "
if(pred_lab[0][2] > 0.5):
    prediction = prediction + "Offensive | "
if(pred_lab[0][2] > 0.5):
    prediction = prediction + "Motivational | "

print("\n\n")
print("   |  Model Prediction :", prediction)
print("\n\n")
